# 🧮 Guessing Game

A simple terminal-based number guessing game written in C.

## Features

- Prompts the player to guess a secret number
- Informs whether the guess is too high or too low
- Congratulates the player when the correct number is guessed

## Concepts Practiced

- Variables and data types
- User input (`scanf`)
- Conditional statements (`if`/`else`)
- Comparison operators
- Basic program structure

## Build

```bash
gcc guessing.c -o guessing
```

## Run

```bash
./guessing
```
